\text{Cov}(X,Y) = \text{E}\left( (X-\mu_x)(Y-\mu_y)\right) = \text{E}\left(XY -\mu_yX - \mu_xY + \mu_x\mu_y  \right) = E(XY) - \mu_y\mu_x - \mu_x\mu_y + \mu_x\mu_y = E(XY) - \mu_x\mu_y
\text{E}\left( (X-\mu_x)Y\right) = \text{E}\left(XY - \mu_xY \right) = \text{E}(XY) - \mu_x\text{E}(Y) = \text{E}(XY) -\mu_x\mu_y = \text{Cov}(X,Y)
